text.section:
A corrective action plan shall comply with KRS 224.1-400, 224.1-405, 224.1-510 to 224.1-532, and any administrative regulations promulgated under these statutes, and shall include:
Detailed documentation of the characterization conducted by the applicant to determine the nature and extent of the release or threatened release as required under KRS 224.1-400 and 224.1-405 and a description of any remediation performed on the site;
A description of any corrective action and additional characterization proposed to complete the remediation in accordance with KRS 224.1-400 and 224.1-405, together with a proposed schedule for implementation;
Descriptions of sampling and analysis methods, techniques, and results, and quality assurance methods and controls used or proposed;
A description of measures to protect human health and safety during the remediation;
A plan of action to inform the public about the remediation and redevelopment of the property and to provide for meaningful public comment;
Identification of any limitations on land use or activity proposed for the site;
Identification of any petroleum storage tanks on the site and an outline of how the applicant intends to comply with Subchapter 60 of KRS Chapter 224 and 401 KAR Chapter 42; and
A requirement to update the corrective action plan to characterize and remediate releases discovered or caused during characterization or corrective action.
